Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
swap_well_taps(25.10)                                    swap_well_taps(25.10)

Name
       swap_well_taps - Swaps to custom tap cell to avoid OD spacing rule

Syntax
       swap_well_taps

       [-help]

       [-both_violation <cellName>]

       -cells <cellName>

       [-check_only]

       [-default_cell <defaultCellName>]

       -diffusion_forbidden_spacing <float>

       [-left_violation <cellName>]

       [-right_violation <cellName>]

       [-skip_cells <cellNameList>]

       [-swap_report <reportName>]

       [-violation_report <reportName>]

       Swaps to custom tap cell to avoid OD spacing rule.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each swap_well_taps parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man swap_well_taps.

       -both_violation <cellName>
              Specifies well taps to swap if  only  violating  rules  on  both
              sides.

       -cells <cellNameList>
              Specifies well taps to swap if there is violation of rules.

       -check_only
              Checks violations only without swapping tap cells.

       -default_cell <defaultCellName>
              Swaps to default well tap first.

              Default well tap must be one of cells.

       -diffusion_forbidden_spacing <float>
              Specifies forbidden spacing rule.

       -left_violation <cellName>
              Specifies  well taps to swap if only violating rules on the left
              side.

       -right_violation <cellName>
              Specifies well taps to swap if only violating rules on the right
              side.

       -skip_cells <cellNameList >
              Specifies the cell that would skip the rule check.

       -swap_report <reportName>
              Reports the swapped instances.

       -violation_report <reportName>
              Reports the violated instances.

Related Information
              * addWellTap

              * set_well_tap_mode

